Vice President Pence delivers remarks at the State Department to welcome Prime Minister Mitsotakis of Greece. He thanks Secretary of State Mike Pompeo for his hospitality and welcomes the Greek American community. Pence highlights the strong bonds between the US and Greece, both economically and philosophically, emphasizing the leadership of President Trump and Prime Minister Mitsotakis. He praises the booming economies of both countries and the low unemployment rates. Pence also reflects on the historical ties between the two nations and the influence of Greek civilization on American ideals of freedom and democracy. He mentions his visit to Greece and expresses his desire to return. Pence concludes by toasting to the enduring friendship between the US and Greece.